article.headline: Mercer 75, Jacksonville 62
article.story: MACON, Ga. (AP) -- James Odoms scored 20 points, hitting 5-of-6 3-pointers, to lead Mercer to a 75-62 victory over Jacksonville on Sunday. The Bears (10-12, 7-6 Atlantic Sun) took the lead for good with 4:46 left in the first half on Jay January's jumper to make it 24-22. Mercer stretched its lead to 33-25 at halftime and Jacksonville (9-11, 4-9) never got closer than four points in the second half. Senior Nolan McBride led the Dolphins with a career-high 23 ponts and Haminn Quaintance added 13. Scott Emerson added 10 points and 10 rebounds for Mercer and Andrew Brown scored 12.
